text: once upon a time there was a prince who
found his princess he courted and wooed
her with his cowboy boots and leather
jacket and in a very short time they
fell in love soon they married and
prepared to spend the rest of their
lives together they had dreams of being
rock stars traveling the world while
living a storybook romance thinking
they'd live happily ever after they
learned that life isn't always like a
storybook they worked hard at jobs they
didn't love while going days without
seeing each other as they became more
successful in their careers but when
they didn't have to work they left their
native land to explore the world with
each trip they reconnected and
rediscovered their romance and passion
they push their boundaries and did
things like climb to the roof of Africa
and paddle at the bottom of the world
they cycled an entire continent did
things that scared them saw things that
moved them and enjoy quiet and memorable
moments in faraway places soon they were
back on track to live happily ever after
but over time their life became more
about work and less about each other and
their passion for travel long hours
behind a computer made them anxious and
busy schedules catching planes and
sleeping in tight quarters exhausted
them so the prince and princess searched
for a fairytale Kingdom that would help
them get back on track they wanted a
land that could capture magic a land
were white knights right up on their
steeds to rescue their fair maidens that
land was Ireland
when planning their time on the emerald
island they could have chosen to jump
off cliffs or go coasteering through
canyons it was expected of them it's
what they do instead this royal couple
went against the wishes of their people
and created their own storybook trip
where they took long walks on the beach
enjoyed the finer things in life and
strolled hand and hand through gardens
and quiet coastal trails Ireland was
their storybook it was a land of beauty
beyond their expectations it was a land
of magic and castles and fairy tales it
was travel to Ireland that made them
feel alive and excited again life on the
road rushing from one destination to the
next was not how they wanted to live
they didn't know until they slowed down
but once again it was travel that
brought Dave and Deb closely together
and they are now prepared for the next
chapter of their storybook romance
